00:55.819 --> 00:57.053
Taylor Berkhalter.

00:57.087 --> 00:58.554
You can't be here
for an appointment.

00:58.588 --> 01:00.623
Well, I'm here on business,
actually.

01:00.657 --> 01:02.158
I'm buying the salon.

01:02.192 --> 01:04.293
This morning, I went to the bank
to try to get a loan.

01:04.328 --> 01:06.462
What in the world for?
I want to buy the salon.

01:06.496 --> 01:08.197
I've always wanted
to do this.

01:08.231 --> 01:09.532
Will you just
do me one favor?

01:09.566 --> 01:11.600
Stay as far away from me
as possible.

01:11.635 --> 01:13.102
We give each other
some space,

01:13.136 --> 01:14.970
and hopefully we won't wind up
killing each other, okay?

01:15.005 --> 01:17.073
Evan? Selena Ramos.

01:17.107 --> 01:19.108
I work with your sister-in-law
at the spa.

01:19.142 --> 01:20.943
I wanted to apologize.
What for?

01:20.977 --> 01:22.578
For putting you
in the position

01:22.612 --> 01:24.547
to feel like you needed
to look after me and the kids.

01:24.581 --> 01:27.783
I hope you know
that you can still count on me.

01:27.818 --> 01:29.185
I know that.

01:29.219 --> 01:30.786
And I hear you have
a young lady joining us tonight.

01:30.821 --> 01:32.621
Why, yes.
Where is she?

01:32.656 --> 01:34.657
I know -- I'm late.

01:35.000 --> 01:38.074
Subtitles downloaded from Podnapisi.NET

01:41.098 --> 01:45.134
♪ I got a secret
I gotta tell you ♪

01:45.168 --> 01:47.636
♪ we're gonna make it

01:47.671 --> 01:51.941
♪ just let me show you how

01:51.975 --> 01:55.478
♪ calm down

01:58.081 --> 02:02.585
♪ little reminder,
everything's fine, yeah ♪

02:02.619 --> 02:04.453
♪ why the sad look, love?

02:04.488 --> 02:07.757
♪ You look better smiling, oh

02:09.860 --> 02:11.527
♪ so listen good

02:14.598 --> 02:17.867
♪ I got a feelin'...

02:17.901 --> 02:19.034
Riley: Hey.

02:19.069 --> 02:21.170
What's up, besides you?

02:23.140 --> 02:25.174
Baby, are you crying?

02:25.208 --> 02:29.311
Mom, I'd know if I was crying,
and I'm not a baby.

02:29.346 --> 02:31.747
Okay.

02:31.782 --> 02:33.816
You're right.

02:33.850 --> 02:35.785
Hey, how about
I rub your back?

02:35.819 --> 02:38.587
Tell me again
why daddy left.

02:39.990 --> 02:43.025
Okay. Uh...

02:43.059 --> 02:46.028
You know how you were --

02:46.062 --> 02:47.963
you were trying to solve
your word problems

02:47.998 --> 02:49.632
the other night?

02:49.666 --> 02:51.066
What do word problems
have to do with anything?

02:51.101 --> 02:54.870
I'm trying to explain to you
why your daddy left,

02:54.905 --> 02:56.172
why he was so confused.

02:56.206 --> 02:58.707
Except...

02:58.742 --> 02:59.775
[ Sighs ]

02:59.810 --> 03:02.478
For him,
it wasn't word problems.

03:02.512 --> 03:04.780
He had other problems
that he couldn't solve.

03:04.815 --> 03:05.881
That's like quitting.

03:05.916 --> 03:08.617
Yeah.
It's kind of like quitting.

03:08.652 --> 03:10.753
Yeah.

03:10.787 --> 03:12.154
I'm not tired.

03:13.857 --> 03:15.324
Okay.

03:15.358 --> 03:16.992
Why don't I just sit here
and rub your back

03:17.027 --> 03:18.127
until you drift off?

03:20.230 --> 03:22.031
He shouldn't have left.

03:39.883 --> 03:41.317
Derek?
Hi. I'm Riley.

03:41.351 --> 03:43.919
I understand you're friends
with Nelson Granger.

03:43.954 --> 03:45.955
Friends
when we're not competing.

03:45.989 --> 03:47.590
Oh, the rodeo?
Yes, ma'am.

03:47.624 --> 03:50.226
Okay, cowboy.
What'd you come in for?

03:50.260 --> 03:52.027
Arms, shoulders, back?

03:52.062 --> 03:53.429
Um...

03:53.463 --> 03:55.197
Truth is, I'm having
some girl trouble.

03:55.232 --> 03:56.966
Oh. Somebody break
your heart?

03:57.000 --> 03:58.467
[ Laughs ]

03:58.502 --> 04:01.403
Well, I've been seeing
my girl, Skyler,

04:01.438 --> 04:04.173
for about six months,
and, uh, things are going good.

04:04.207 --> 04:06.108
In fact, we just
moved in together.

04:06.142 --> 04:08.344
Sounds like they're going
better than good.

04:08.378 --> 04:10.079
[ Laughs ]

04:10.113 --> 04:12.982
I thought so, until she started
laying down some rules.

04:13.016 --> 04:14.984
Ah. Let me guess --
"Don't put that over there"

04:15.018 --> 04:17.119
and "Don't drink
from that carton" kind of rules?

04:17.153 --> 04:19.387
Really,
just one in particular.

04:19.422 --> 04:22.024
She wants me
to give up rodeo'ing.

04:22.058 --> 04:23.859
She's too afraid
I'll get hurt.

04:23.894 --> 04:26.128
Well, I can understand
her being concerned.

04:26.162 --> 04:27.663
Oh, I can, too.
Trust me.

04:27.697 --> 04:29.865
Riding's got its risks,
but it's just like anything.

04:29.900 --> 04:32.067
Yeah, except you can't
get a hoof to the head

04:32.102 --> 04:33.435
unless you're in the ring.

04:33.470 --> 04:35.237
Get hit by a bus
just crossing the street.

04:35.272 --> 04:37.006
So what'd she say
about it?

04:37.040 --> 04:38.807
She won't listen.

04:38.842 --> 04:42.244
Which brings me to what I'm
doing here in the first place.

04:42.279 --> 04:45.047
Skyler says she's not,
um...

04:45.081 --> 04:48.817
Well, we're not having,
uh...relations

04:48.852 --> 04:52.221
until I agree to give up
rodeo riding altogether.

04:52.255 --> 04:55.157
Wow. She's playing hardball --
so to speak.

04:55.191 --> 04:56.992
I'm not giving in
without a fight.

04:57.027 --> 04:58.694
How's that?

04:58.728 --> 05:00.863
Skyler thinks I can't last
two days without her,

05:00.897 --> 05:04.400
but, thanks to my buddy
who recommended you,

05:04.434 --> 05:06.402
she doesn't know
I got a secret weapon.

05:21.451 --> 05:24.019
Evan: Yeah,
I'll take a quart of that,

05:24.054 --> 05:26.288
extra barbecue sauce,
and coleslaw.

05:26.323 --> 05:29.124
Man: You got it.

05:29.159 --> 05:31.427
Can I get
an iced tea?

05:31.461 --> 05:32.995
You really think
that'll sit well?

05:33.029 --> 05:34.063
[ Laughs ]

05:34.097 --> 05:35.364
Hey.

05:35.398 --> 05:36.932
You make that
two iced teas, hon.

05:36.967 --> 05:38.334
Hi.
What are you doing here?

05:38.368 --> 05:40.069
I saw your truck,
so I just turned around.

05:40.103 --> 05:42.004
You on your way
to work?

05:42.038 --> 05:43.305
Indeed I am.

05:43.340 --> 05:45.174
I got to tell you,

05:45.208 --> 05:46.976
I don't know how you and Riley
manage that commute every day.

05:47.010 --> 05:48.377
That is
a long and boring drive.

05:48.411 --> 05:50.012
Eh, drive's not so bad.

05:50.046 --> 05:52.281
I just get my mind to wandering
and start daydreaming.

05:52.315 --> 05:54.049
Yeah?
Yeah. [ Laughs ]

05:54.084 --> 05:56.218
Well, I'll be sure to remember
that and steer clear.

05:56.252 --> 05:57.419
[ Laughing ] Okay.

05:57.454 --> 05:58.954
Iced tea is over here.

05:58.989 --> 06:00.255
Okay!

06:00.290 --> 06:03.025
So, listen, um,
speaking of daydreaming,

06:03.059 --> 06:05.127
I was thinking about dinner
the other night.

06:06.162 --> 06:07.529
Yeah.

06:07.564 --> 06:09.398
I was just wondering if --
I don't know,

06:09.432 --> 06:12.301
maybe you'd like to go away
for the weekend sometime.

06:15.238 --> 06:17.439
Uh...that sounds...

06:17.474 --> 06:18.507
sounds good.

06:18.541 --> 06:20.242
Just...

06:20.276 --> 06:21.910
Yeah, I just started
this new job.

06:21.945 --> 06:23.479
Yeah. Well, maybe when
you're not busy or, you know?

06:23.513 --> 06:25.147
I got to --
I should get to work.

06:25.181 --> 06:26.382
I got
that long drive --

06:26.416 --> 06:27.850
thought that was you.
[ Laughs ]

06:27.884 --> 06:29.251
Hey.
What's up, Danny?

06:29.285 --> 06:30.853
Not very warm and fuzzy.

06:30.887 --> 06:33.055
Hey, hands off. Come on.
Hands off?

06:33.089 --> 06:35.457
Funny -- that's not
what you said last night.

06:35.492 --> 06:37.226
Hey, hey, cool, okay?
Leave her alone, man.

06:37.260 --> 06:38.560
Who made you bodyguard?

06:38.595 --> 06:40.729
Just get out of my way.
Get out of my way!

06:42.198 --> 06:43.866
Evan:
I'll talk to you later, Selena.

06:46.536 --> 06:49.538
[ Engine turns over,
car departs ]

06:55.578 --> 06:57.312
Georgia: Somebody help!
- Coming.

06:57.347 --> 07:00.049
[ Muffled ] Hang on.
Come on! I can't see where I'm going!

07:00.083 --> 07:01.283
I don't want
to break it.

07:01.317 --> 07:03.786
Oh, my goodness!
Oh, my God.

07:03.820 --> 07:06.288
Put it right here.
Ah! Okay!

07:06.322 --> 07:08.157
Well, whose are these,
anyway?

07:08.191 --> 07:09.191
Dee Ann.

07:09.225 --> 07:10.793
Me?

07:10.827 --> 07:12.828
Well, that's what the man said
who delivered them.

07:12.862 --> 07:15.464
Are you sure there isn't
some kind of mistake?

07:15.498 --> 07:16.999
They're so beautiful.

07:17.033 --> 07:18.934
Could be a floating
Rose Bowl parade.

07:18.968 --> 07:20.235
No card?

07:20.270 --> 07:22.104
[ Gasps ]
Oh, no. Who died?

07:22.138 --> 07:23.172
Nobody died!

07:23.206 --> 07:24.973
Oh. Then who's
getting married?

07:25.008 --> 07:26.809
Well, that's it.
They're for Kendra.

07:26.843 --> 07:29.211
Will you stop trying
to give your flowers away?

07:29.245 --> 07:30.245
These are yours!

07:30.280 --> 07:31.447
Yeah,
I'm with Georgia.

07:31.481 --> 07:32.614
Besides,
I don't think Kendra eloped.

07:33.516 --> 07:35.384
Oh, hell to the no!

07:35.418 --> 07:38.087
Georgia!
It's a relaxing game.

07:38.121 --> 07:40.222
The only ones that's supposed to
be relaxing around here

07:40.256 --> 07:41.190
are the clients!

07:41.224 --> 07:42.458
Understood?

07:42.492 --> 07:44.126
Give me those.
Give!

07:44.160 --> 07:45.828
[ Sighs ]

07:45.862 --> 07:47.496
Tearing up my walls.

07:47.530 --> 07:49.531
This place costs too much
to be bothering with hanging up

07:49.566 --> 07:51.400
stuff on the wall
that ain't supposed to be there.

07:51.434 --> 07:52.935
Get to work!

07:52.969 --> 07:55.304
Wow.
They really are pretty.

08:04.614 --> 08:07.116
Lacey: What do you think
they're saying?

08:07.150 --> 08:08.584
I haven't got a clue.

08:08.618 --> 08:10.919
Bet they're talking about Taylor
wanting to buy the salon.

08:10.954 --> 08:12.421
'Course they're talking about
Taylor wanting to buy the salon.

08:12.455 --> 08:13.956
Hi, mama.
[ Gasps ]

08:13.990 --> 08:15.924
Riley, stop sneaking up on me
like that.

08:15.959 --> 08:17.559
Um, you were too busy
watching Taylor.

08:17.594 --> 08:18.894
I mean,
a bomb could go off

08:18.928 --> 08:20.095
and neither one of you
would know it.

08:20.130 --> 08:21.029
Hush!

08:21.064 --> 08:22.297
Now, where's Travis?

08:22.332 --> 08:23.465
How should I know?

08:23.500 --> 08:24.900
Uh, I left him here
with you.

08:24.934 --> 08:27.035
Just thinking about working
for that bottle blonde

08:27.070 --> 08:28.370
makes me dizzy.

08:28.404 --> 08:29.371
Okay, you're gonna
have to snap out of it.

08:29.405 --> 08:31.106
Oh, I'll be fine.

08:31.141 --> 08:33.876
I'd be better if a comet fell
out of the sky and hit Taylor.

08:33.909 --> 08:35.409
She's not the nicest.
I'll give you that.

08:35.445 --> 08:37.546
She's probably plotting
how to get rid of me right now.

08:37.580 --> 08:39.548
Do you really think she's
gonna take over the salon?

08:39.582 --> 08:40.948
Not if I can help it.

08:40.984 --> 08:42.417
What are you
thinking of doing?

08:42.452 --> 08:44.219
I don't want to count my
chickens before they're hatched,

08:44.254 --> 08:46.622
but I've been talking to
Mr. Richardson down at the bank,

08:46.656 --> 08:48.624
and I'm gonna try
and buy the salon.

08:48.658 --> 08:51.026
I think he's gonna have
good news for me.

08:51.060 --> 08:53.896
After all, I bought Walmart
before it split back in 1999.

08:56.099 --> 08:57.132
[ Gasps ]

08:57.167 --> 08:59.468
Oh, my --
what are you doing?!

08:59.502 --> 09:01.069
Hey,
is everything okay?

09:01.104 --> 09:03.639
No! It is most certainly
not okay.

09:03.673 --> 09:07.442
I just caught your son
taking advantage of my daughter!

09:07.477 --> 09:09.111
Well, come on, kids.

09:09.145 --> 09:10.879
Let's go play astronaut
under the hair dryers.

09:10.914 --> 09:12.247
[ Sighs ]
Okay.

09:12.282 --> 09:15.017
Taylor, I'm sure they weren't
doing anything wrong.

09:15.051 --> 09:16.418
I know what I saw.

09:16.452 --> 09:18.086
What is it
that you think you saw?

09:18.121 --> 09:21.490
Twinkle had her skirt up,
and Travis was looking at it.

09:21.524 --> 09:23.492
Taylor,
kids get curious.

09:23.526 --> 09:25.127
Not my kid.

09:25.161 --> 09:27.462
Are you trying to say
that this is all Travis' doing?

09:27.497 --> 09:29.431
I am saying
this is exactly what happens

09:29.465 --> 09:31.567
when a boy does not have
a proper male role model

09:31.601 --> 09:32.634
in the house.

09:33.970 --> 09:34.837
Wow.

09:36.539 --> 09:39.274
Get up!
We are leaving!

09:41.177 --> 09:42.578
Come on!

09:48.786 --> 09:50.821
Riley: And then Taylor told me
that my son needs

09:50.855 --> 09:52.990
a stronger male influence
in his life.

09:53.024 --> 09:55.192
Ooh. Talk about
hitting below the belt.

09:55.226 --> 09:57.160
Husband, wife,
father, mother --

09:57.195 --> 09:59.196
that is how
it seems to work best --

09:59.230 --> 10:00.564
I mean, in my opinion,
anyway.

10:00.598 --> 10:02.265
My daddy died
when I was 8.

10:02.300 --> 10:03.900
Is that how
it's supposed to be?

10:05.169 --> 10:06.236
Oh!

10:06.270 --> 10:07.104
[ Groans ]

10:07.138 --> 10:08.372
Hey.

10:08.406 --> 10:09.940
You know what?

10:09.974 --> 10:12.743
And I don't need her
to remind me that Kyle's gone.

10:12.777 --> 10:14.978
I mean, Travis cried
the other night.

10:15.013 --> 10:16.313
That's reminder enough.

10:16.347 --> 10:17.948
There's no reason to believe
anything unsavory

10:17.982 --> 10:19.383
happened between Travis
and that little girl.

10:19.417 --> 10:22.653
I mean, I even played nurse
when I was a child.

10:22.687 --> 10:25.322
Oh, there's nothing innocent
about boys and girls

10:25.356 --> 10:26.456
when they get together.

10:27.525 --> 10:28.892
Well, I'm just saying,
these days,

10:28.926 --> 10:30.627
with the Internet
and all the social media,

10:30.662 --> 10:32.329
kids are starting
younger and younger.

10:32.363 --> 10:34.031
I don't know.

10:34.065 --> 10:35.699
I think boys are just born
with a sexual appetite,

10:35.733 --> 10:37.634
and we grow up
and learn how to manipulate it.

10:37.669 --> 10:40.170
Well, I'm sure Eddie Snedeker
still thinks about

10:40.204 --> 10:41.672
that little piece of heaven
I gave to him

10:41.706 --> 10:43.440
back in the eighth grade.

10:43.474 --> 10:45.275
Okay, we are trying to have
an intelligent conversation here.

10:45.309 --> 10:46.376
Do you mind?

10:47.412 --> 10:48.845
Well, pardon me.

10:48.880 --> 10:50.414
Riley: I mean,
it's like what we do here.

10:50.448 --> 10:52.649
You know, these guys
feel like they're craving

10:52.684 --> 10:55.218
some sort of physical touch,
and they come see us.

10:55.253 --> 10:56.887
And they pay us.
I wouldn't know.

10:56.921 --> 10:58.422
Selena:
Oh, the men you massage

10:58.456 --> 11:00.624
are just the same
as the men we massage.

11:00.658 --> 11:03.126
They are not!
There is a big difference.

11:03.161 --> 11:04.361
Yeah -- this big.

11:04.395 --> 11:05.696
[ Laughter ]

11:05.730 --> 11:07.030
Jolene:
I thought we were having

11:07.065 --> 11:08.298
an intelligent conversation
about sex.

11:08.332 --> 11:10.233
I remember my mother
tried convincing me

11:10.268 --> 11:11.668
that babies
came from storks.

11:11.703 --> 11:14.137
I mean, actually flown in,
tied to some bird's beak.

11:14.172 --> 11:16.473
Please. My mama couldn't even look
me in the eye and tell me about it.

11:16.507 --> 11:17.574
She wrote me a letter.

11:17.608 --> 11:18.742
I think
that's kind of sweet.

11:18.776 --> 11:20.010
Not if you read
what she wrote --

11:20.044 --> 11:21.578
or saw
the pictures she drew.

11:21.612 --> 11:23.046
It even scared me
out of sex.

11:23.081 --> 11:24.314
Couldn't have been
for too long.

11:24.348 --> 11:25.682
Minutes.

11:25.717 --> 11:27.217
How y'all doing
this morning?

11:27.251 --> 11:29.286
Riley,
someone's here to see you.

11:29.320 --> 11:31.288
It's either the wife or the
girlfriend of one of your clients.

11:31.322 --> 11:33.123
How do you know?

11:33.157 --> 11:34.725
Honey, when you've been
working here as long as I have,

11:34.759 --> 11:36.993
you can see them coming
a mile down the road.

11:37.028 --> 11:39.129
[ Sighs ]

11:43.401 --> 11:45.402
Hi. I'm Riley.

11:45.436 --> 11:47.337
My boyfriend said you gave him
a massage yesterday --

11:47.371 --> 11:48.605
Derek West.

11:48.639 --> 11:50.040
Oh, yeah --
rodeo cowboy.

11:50.074 --> 11:51.575
Right, so let's skip
the nicey-nice,

11:51.609 --> 11:54.144
'cause I'm pretty sure I know
what he came looking for,

11:54.178 --> 11:55.579
and I want it to stop.

11:55.613 --> 11:57.247
Men and women
come into this spa

11:57.281 --> 11:59.449
to clear their minds
and heal their bodies.

11:59.484 --> 12:01.618
We've got nothing to do
with their hearts.

12:03.287 --> 12:04.988
My name's Skyler.

12:05.022 --> 12:06.423
And I love
my boyfriend,

12:06.457 --> 12:08.725
but we are having
a big disagreement.

12:08.760 --> 12:11.428
When it comes to what he cares
about most, you or the rodeo,

12:11.462 --> 12:13.230
do you really want
to make him choose?

12:13.264 --> 12:14.731
You think
it's wrong for me

12:14.766 --> 12:16.433
to want him to stay
in one piece?

12:16.467 --> 12:18.568
No, I think you're wrong for
withholding affection from him

12:18.603 --> 12:19.903
and using sex
to get what you want.

12:19.937 --> 12:22.472
I miss Derek
just as much as he misses me.

12:22.507 --> 12:23.940
But if he's gonna keep
seeing you,

12:23.975 --> 12:25.809
then it's gonna be the end
for the two of us.

12:25.843 --> 12:27.477
You really want that
on your conscience?

12:27.512 --> 12:29.780
You're gonna do whatever you
have to, but don't threaten me.

12:33.518 --> 12:36.353
[ Sighs ] I guess I'm not
gonna be the poster girl

12:36.387 --> 12:37.721
for your spa anytime soon.

12:37.755 --> 12:39.523
Well, you're bound
to run into problems

12:39.557 --> 12:42.125
when you're dealing with folk
not wearing their clothes.

12:42.160 --> 12:44.361
Think about it -- they're lying
there on your table,

12:44.395 --> 12:47.898
as exposed and open
as the day they were born.

12:47.932 --> 12:49.332
Yeah. Maybe I should be
more sensitive.

12:49.367 --> 12:50.500
Oh, please.

12:50.535 --> 12:52.969
I think you make
a great poster girl.

13:05.616 --> 13:06.650
Hey.

13:08.252 --> 13:09.619
[ Chuckles ]

13:09.654 --> 13:11.288
What the heck are you doing
this far from Beaumont?

13:11.322 --> 13:12.956
You, um...

13:14.392 --> 13:15.792
you forgot
your iced tea.

13:15.827 --> 13:18.628
You, Mr. Parks,
are much too kind.

13:18.663 --> 13:20.764
Now, seriously, what are you
doing so far away from home?

13:20.798 --> 13:22.199
I got a job
not too far from here,

13:22.233 --> 13:24.367
and I just wanted to talk to you
about the other day.

13:24.402 --> 13:25.735
You know what?

13:25.770 --> 13:28.038
We don't have to do that.
It's okay.

13:28.072 --> 13:30.807
Three calls to your cell,
not one of them returned?

13:30.842 --> 13:32.676
It was me inviting you
away for the weekend.

13:32.710 --> 13:34.144
It was just too soon.

13:34.178 --> 13:35.579
Maybe.

13:37.381 --> 13:39.182
But...

13:39.217 --> 13:41.284
But what?

13:43.354 --> 13:44.321
[ Chuckles ]

13:44.355 --> 13:46.122
[ Chuckles ]

13:46.157 --> 13:49.626
I was embarrassed. That's why
I didn't call you back.

13:49.660 --> 13:52.162
Well, I was embarrassed I didn't know
what to say when you asked me.

13:52.196 --> 13:53.530
Well, I guess
we're in the same spot, then.

13:53.564 --> 13:54.631
Well, I guess we are.

13:54.665 --> 13:56.032
Okay. [ Laughs ]

13:57.969 --> 13:59.769
So, this is where
you and Riley work, huh?

13:59.804 --> 14:01.471
Yes.

14:01.505 --> 14:03.607
Now, I know it doesn't
look like much on the outside,

14:03.641 --> 14:05.642
but the inside's --
it's okay.

14:05.676 --> 14:07.277
You don't want
to take a peek?

14:09.714 --> 14:11.248
Why not?

14:11.282 --> 14:13.283
I got nothing but miles
of blacktop waiting for me.

14:13.317 --> 14:15.051
All right.
Come on.

14:18.022 --> 14:19.656
[ Chuckles ] Thank you.
Mm-hmm.

14:19.690 --> 14:22.259
All right, this way.

14:22.293 --> 14:23.126
Hey, you.

14:24.495 --> 14:25.795
Evan.

14:25.830 --> 14:27.664
[ Chuckles ]
Well, Riley, it looks like

14:27.698 --> 14:29.499
you bumped into
the ghost of Sam Houston.

14:29.533 --> 14:31.434
Just surprised.

14:31.469 --> 14:32.936
That's all.

14:32.970 --> 14:34.604
So, do you need directions
getting home?

14:34.639 --> 14:36.406
[ Laughs ]

14:36.440 --> 14:38.408
Selena was right -- this place
is a whole different world

14:38.442 --> 14:39.542
once you step inside.

14:39.577 --> 14:41.645
Oh,
you have no idea.

14:43.414 --> 14:45.315
- How about I show you around?
- Yeah, maybe another time.

14:45.349 --> 14:46.816
Riley, when am I
gonna get back up here?

14:46.851 --> 14:48.618
Yeah, Riley.
Stop spoiling all the fun.

14:48.653 --> 14:50.186
Well, it's pizza night,

14:50.221 --> 14:52.022
and the kids are expecting me
to come over,

14:52.056 --> 14:53.556
so who wants to eat
cold pizza?

14:53.591 --> 14:55.592
[ Laughs ]

14:55.626 --> 14:57.427
Yeah, no one I know.

14:58.763 --> 15:02.732
You know what? I'll, uh...
I'll talk to you later.

15:04.201 --> 15:05.502
Okay.

15:06.470 --> 15:08.305
Bye.

15:08.339 --> 15:10.607
You can screw with me
all you want.

15:10.641 --> 15:12.275
You can even screw Evan,

15:12.310 --> 15:14.010
because he is a grown man
who can take care of himself.

15:14.045 --> 15:15.645
But if you ever
bring him here again,

15:15.680 --> 15:17.614
I swear to God,
you will live to regret it.

15:32.229 --> 15:34.431
Hey! Mee maw's
bringing pizza.

15:34.465 --> 15:35.498
Pepperoni?

15:35.533 --> 15:37.300
Half and half.

15:37.335 --> 15:39.436
And I just ran into Uncle Evan.
He's gonna come by, too.

15:39.470 --> 15:41.604
Okay.

15:41.639 --> 15:43.073
Hey, you know what?

15:43.107 --> 15:45.442
Um...Mrs. Berkhalter
and I --

15:45.476 --> 15:48.511
we didn't mean to embarrass you
the other day at the salon.

15:48.546 --> 15:49.546
You didn't.

15:49.580 --> 15:50.847
Oh.

15:50.881 --> 15:52.849
Okay. Good.

15:52.883 --> 15:54.751
You think
Twinkle was upset?

15:54.785 --> 15:57.120
I don't know.

15:59.156 --> 16:02.292
What were you guys doing
in that room, anyway?

16:02.326 --> 16:04.361
Nothing, mom. Geez!

16:04.395 --> 16:05.662
Okay. Sorry.

16:05.696 --> 16:07.097
[ Door opens, closes ]

16:07.131 --> 16:08.798
Evan:
Where is everybody?

16:08.833 --> 16:11.701
Can you go ask Uncle Evan
if he'll come up and help me?

16:11.736 --> 16:12.736
Sure, baby.

16:12.770 --> 16:14.270
Mom!

16:14.305 --> 16:16.806
Okay, I'm sorry.
I know you're not a baby.

16:18.409 --> 16:19.909
Okay.

16:23.280 --> 16:25.382
So,
you made your way back.

16:25.416 --> 16:28.385
What was that all about,
you and Selena?

16:28.419 --> 16:29.886
Nothing. Forget it.

16:29.920 --> 16:32.655
You know what? Why did you
bring her the other night?

16:32.690 --> 16:35.158
Maybe if you just let me know
that she was gonna be there,

16:35.192 --> 16:36.526
it would have made it
easier.

16:36.560 --> 16:37.927
Although
I pretty much doubt it.

16:37.962 --> 16:39.529
I thought
you two were friends.

16:39.563 --> 16:40.864
It's complicated.

16:40.898 --> 16:42.265
She's a nice girl.

16:43.534 --> 16:44.534
Nice enough.

16:44.568 --> 16:45.535
Evan, you have never
dated nice.

16:45.569 --> 16:46.936
Questionable.

16:46.971 --> 16:48.471
I know you don't
have to be around Selena long

16:48.506 --> 16:51.274
to realize that she's a little
rough around the edges.

16:51.308 --> 16:52.809
Now you're
just being kind.

16:52.843 --> 16:54.844
Maybe that's part
of what I like about her.

16:54.879 --> 16:56.446
I ran into her earlier.

16:56.480 --> 16:58.648
I needed to talk to her
about something,

16:58.682 --> 17:00.417
so I came by the spa.

17:00.451 --> 17:01.918
Next time,
take a cold shower.

17:01.952 --> 17:03.887
What were you doing
in Sugar Land, anyway?

17:03.921 --> 17:05.888
I had a job.
What kind of job?

17:05.923 --> 17:07.924
Berkhalter has
a construction site

17:07.958 --> 17:09.692
not too far
from Mission Bend.

17:09.727 --> 17:11.327
Well, there you go.

17:11.362 --> 17:12.762
Maybe you should
spend more time

17:12.797 --> 17:14.864
on something you're actually
getting paid to do.

17:14.898 --> 17:17.300
What has got you
so fired up?

17:17.334 --> 17:19.602
Nothing.
It's none of my concern.

17:21.972 --> 17:24.707
By the way, Travis was found
in a room with Twinkle.

17:24.742 --> 17:26.342
Maybe Taylor's right.

17:26.377 --> 17:28.678
Maybe he does need
a man around here to talk to.

17:28.712 --> 17:30.680
Well, how about tomorrow
I take him fishing?

17:30.714 --> 17:32.549
We haven't been up to the lake
in a while,

17:32.583 --> 17:35.652
and, you know, give him a chance
to open up if he needs to.

17:35.686 --> 17:36.719
You would do that?

17:36.754 --> 17:39.155
Riley, of course.

17:39.190 --> 17:40.557
Well,
what are you gonna say?

17:42.660 --> 17:44.427
I mean, that is not
a good game plan.

17:44.462 --> 17:45.728
Well,
guys don't like to talk.

17:47.264 --> 17:48.665
I mean...we talk.

17:48.699 --> 17:51.801
We just -- we don't do it
face-to-face like this.

17:51.836 --> 17:54.337
We do it shoulder-to-shoulder --
you know,

17:54.371 --> 17:58.074
like when you're fishing
or working or driving a car.

17:59.577 --> 18:00.877
Thank you.

18:01.979 --> 18:03.213
[ Door opens ]

18:03.247 --> 18:04.814
Linette:
Come and get it!

18:04.849 --> 18:06.716
Hey, mama.
Hey, baby.

18:06.750 --> 18:09.786
Evan, your date the other night
was delightful,

18:09.820 --> 18:11.321
if not a little brassy.

18:11.355 --> 18:12.722
Yeah, we're not talking
about Selena anymore.

18:12.756 --> 18:14.424
Katie! Travis!
Mee maw's here!

18:14.458 --> 18:15.758
With pizza!
Come on! Let's eat!

18:15.793 --> 18:17.227
I didn't drive
like a bat out of hell

18:17.261 --> 18:18.428
to eat cold, soggy pizza!

18:18.462 --> 18:19.429
Where are y'all?!

18:19.463 --> 18:20.330
Hey.

18:21.832 --> 18:25.101
Be careful with Selena.

18:41.875 --> 18:44.943
Riley: I was pretty surprised to see
that you were on my schedule

18:44.978 --> 18:47.412
and a little disappointed
to see that things

18:47.447 --> 18:49.982
weren't working out so well
with you and Skyler.

18:50.016 --> 18:51.850
[ Sighs ]

18:51.885 --> 18:54.019
I'm embarrassed
to even say it,

18:54.053 --> 18:56.555
but she got herself
a massager --

18:56.589 --> 18:57.556
vibrator.

18:57.590 --> 18:58.790
I know. I know.

18:58.825 --> 19:00.392
It's my fault,
I guess.

19:00.426 --> 19:02.761
Look,
Skyler came to see me.

19:02.795 --> 19:06.565
She was pretty determined
that you're not gonna be riding.

19:06.599 --> 19:08.567
[ Sighs ]

19:08.601 --> 19:11.503
I just...

19:11.537 --> 19:13.572
I don't know any way
to fix this.

19:13.606 --> 19:15.374
The weird thing is,

19:15.408 --> 19:17.242
it's not even the sex
that I miss.

19:18.978 --> 19:20.812
I miss
the smell of her hair,

19:20.847 --> 19:23.015
the way
she scrunches up her nose

19:23.049 --> 19:24.950
when she laughs
at my jokes --

19:24.984 --> 19:26.585
even the bad ones.

19:26.619 --> 19:27.853
[ Chuckles ]

19:27.887 --> 19:29.688
That's 'cause
you two have a connection.

19:31.424 --> 19:34.026
You better fix this --
and quick.

19:34.060 --> 19:36.028
Otherwise...

19:36.062 --> 19:37.729
trust me --
you'll regret it.

19:44.971 --> 19:46.738
Thank you.

19:57.083 --> 19:58.550
You're welcome.

19:58.584 --> 20:00.252
Kyle: Well, girl,
what are you doing?

20:00.286 --> 20:01.887
What's taking you so long?
Come on.

20:01.921 --> 20:04.423
Will you just hold your horses?
I'll be out in a minute.

20:04.457 --> 20:06.892
You said that
15 minutes ago.

20:06.926 --> 20:09.728
I'm gonna start this
without you.

20:09.762 --> 20:10.696
Okay, you ready?

20:10.730 --> 20:12.798
For what?

20:15.802 --> 20:17.002
Ta-da!

20:17.036 --> 20:18.937
[ Chuckles ]

20:18.972 --> 20:20.906
What?

20:22.809 --> 20:25.711
Baby, w-where did all that
come from?

20:25.745 --> 20:26.878
And how much
did that cost?

20:26.913 --> 20:28.013
[ Sighs ]

20:28.047 --> 20:29.581
Shoot.
This is not sexy at all.

20:29.615 --> 20:30.882
Oh, no.

20:30.917 --> 20:32.417
I love it.

20:33.519 --> 20:37.756
Well, I was just, you know,
trying to spice things up.

20:37.790 --> 20:40.692
So...get to spicing.

20:40.727 --> 20:42.627
Really?

20:42.662 --> 20:44.062
Yeah.

20:44.097 --> 20:46.798
Come on, girl.
Let's see what you got.

20:46.833 --> 20:48.433
[ Sighs ]

20:48.468 --> 20:49.935
Okay.

20:49.969 --> 20:53.005
Well,
if I was to do this,

20:53.039 --> 20:56.241
would you buy me
something really pretty

20:56.275 --> 20:58.510
to wear
for our anniversary dinner?

20:58.544 --> 20:59.611
[ Laughs ]

20:59.645 --> 21:01.980
Well, I guess
everything is negotiable.

21:03.583 --> 21:04.649
Good to know.

21:04.684 --> 21:06.485
Mm.

21:06.519 --> 21:08.720
Come on.
Let me see this.

21:08.755 --> 21:09.855
Okay.

21:09.889 --> 21:11.023
Good lord.

21:11.057 --> 21:12.858
What do you think?

21:12.892 --> 21:16.361
I think you can have
whatever you want.

21:16.396 --> 21:17.796
I'm gonna remember
you said that.

21:17.830 --> 21:19.197
Okay.

21:30.576 --> 21:32.544
Do fish sleep
with their eyes open?

21:35.114 --> 21:36.982
That's a good question.

21:37.016 --> 21:39.317
I never really thought
about it.

21:39.352 --> 21:41.920
They sure are quiet today,
though, aren't they?

21:41.954 --> 21:44.322
That's fine.

21:44.357 --> 21:46.658
It's just fun
being here with you.

21:48.161 --> 21:50.362
Well, it's fun
being here with you, too.

21:53.566 --> 21:55.434
So, how's everything going
with your sister?

21:55.468 --> 21:57.035
Fine, I guess.
She's weird.

21:57.070 --> 21:59.871
Yeah. I feel the same way
about a lot of girls, too.

21:59.906 --> 22:01.573
You do?

22:01.607 --> 22:02.841
Mm-hmm.

22:04.610 --> 22:06.978
How about that girl that does
all those beauty pageants?

22:07.013 --> 22:09.047
Twinkle?
Especially her.

22:09.082 --> 22:11.116
But her mom's
even weirder.

22:11.150 --> 22:12.951
Yeah? How so?

22:12.985 --> 22:15.220
The other day, I asked if
I could play dress-up with her.

22:15.254 --> 22:18.723
She said yes, so I took
her dress and pulled it up.

22:18.758 --> 22:19.958
[ Chuckles ]

22:19.992 --> 22:21.760
Then her mom
opened the door.

22:21.794 --> 22:23.528
And saw you guys?

22:23.563 --> 22:26.465
I never heard somebody
scream so loud. It scared me.

22:26.499 --> 22:28.033
Well,
I'm sorry about that.

22:29.502 --> 22:32.170
Eh, like I said,
girls are weird.

22:33.573 --> 22:34.406
Yeah.

22:38.611 --> 22:40.011
I miss my dad.

22:42.448 --> 22:43.782
Yeah,
I miss him, too, bud.

22:46.085 --> 22:48.420
I miss him, too.

22:52.391 --> 22:55.127
Mr. Richardson:
Linette, I'm impressed.

22:55.161 --> 22:57.562
The salon seems
a sound investment.

22:57.597 --> 23:00.599
It could benefit you
well into retirement.

23:00.633 --> 23:02.601
Slow down, Jim. Don't put me
in an old folks' home yet.

23:02.635 --> 23:05.504
Mr. Richardson, I went by
my own bank this morning,

23:05.538 --> 23:08.073
and I would like to help mama
buy the salon.

23:08.107 --> 23:09.808
Honey,
I never asked you --

23:09.842 --> 23:11.042
I'm offering.

23:11.077 --> 23:12.911
From my
preliminary assessment,

23:12.945 --> 23:14.846
you could use the help,
Linette.

23:14.881 --> 23:16.148
Baby,
you can't afford to.

23:16.182 --> 23:17.916
I have been putting money away
on the side.

23:17.950 --> 23:19.651
You two
will be partners.

23:19.685 --> 23:20.719
[ Laughs ]

23:20.753 --> 23:22.654
Partners.
Isn't that something?

23:22.688 --> 23:23.688
Yeah.

23:23.723 --> 23:25.056
All righty, then.

23:25.091 --> 23:26.558
Uh, Riley,
I'm gonna need access

23:26.592 --> 23:28.226
to your personal
financial statements.

23:28.261 --> 23:29.828
Uh, which ones
would those be?

23:29.862 --> 23:32.831
Well, general financials,
assets, liabilities,

23:32.865 --> 23:35.033
proof of income,
uh, tax records --

23:35.067 --> 23:36.568
that sort of thing.

23:36.602 --> 23:39.171
Wow. That's a lot
of personal information.

23:39.205 --> 23:41.239
It's not like she's
running for office or anything.

23:41.274 --> 23:42.941
Yeah. I thought
that I was just gonna,

23:42.975 --> 23:44.309
you know,
give mama the money.

23:44.343 --> 23:46.578
Well, technically,
that would be the way,

23:46.612 --> 23:49.714
but, uh, your generosity
has made you a silent partner,

23:49.749 --> 23:52.317
and as such, you're subject
to the same scrutiny

23:52.351 --> 23:54.486
as any
small-business-loan applicant.

23:56.255 --> 23:58.990
Well, maybe I should just...
go over these at home.

23:59.025 --> 24:01.760
Just get them back to me
as soon as you can.

24:01.794 --> 24:04.095
I wouldn't want your mom
to lose out

24:04.130 --> 24:05.964
because we were slow
to the go.

24:05.998 --> 24:08.567
No. Of course not.

24:08.601 --> 24:10.869
Isn't it great --
partners?

24:10.903 --> 24:12.871
Yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

24:12.905 --> 24:14.706
There you go.

24:16.776 --> 24:18.176
Evan: Mmm!

24:18.211 --> 24:19.978
This is the best barbecue
you will ever taste, Trav --

24:20.012 --> 24:21.046
guaranteed.

24:21.080 --> 24:23.315
[ Tires screech ]

24:26.752 --> 24:27.786
Well, look who it is.

24:28.888 --> 24:30.889
Look, I'm not looking
for any trouble, man,

24:30.923 --> 24:33.658
so why don't you
just take off?

24:33.693 --> 24:34.893
Really, tough guy?

24:34.927 --> 24:37.062
You like telling me
what to do, hmm?

24:37.096 --> 24:39.431
No. Actually, I don't.

24:39.465 --> 24:41.299
There's nothing
I really like about you.

24:41.334 --> 24:42.267
[ Chuckles ]

24:42.301 --> 24:43.868
Where's your girlfriend?

24:43.903 --> 24:46.004
I wouldn't know.

24:46.038 --> 24:47.939
I would.

24:47.974 --> 24:51.610
She's probably off
doing what she does best.

24:51.644 --> 24:53.178
Being a slut.

24:55.381 --> 24:57.315
I'd really love to finish
this conversation right now,

24:57.350 --> 24:59.084
but I got to
get my nephew home,

24:59.118 --> 25:01.052
so why don't you
get the hell out of here?

25:07.260 --> 25:09.628
You ready, buddy?
Buckle up.

25:09.662 --> 25:10.595
Who was that?

25:10.630 --> 25:11.997
Oh, that?

25:12.031 --> 25:13.765
That was
just an old friend.

25:13.799 --> 25:16.067
Yeah, right.

25:16.102 --> 25:18.336
[ Engine turns over ]

25:22.775 --> 25:25.510
[ Door opens, closes ]

25:25.544 --> 25:27.912
Brought barbecue
for dinner.

25:27.947 --> 25:28.980
Oh, hey, thanks.

25:29.015 --> 25:30.048
Hey, baby.
How was fishing?

25:30.082 --> 25:32.183
Uncle Evan decked a guy!

25:32.218 --> 25:33.118
Excuse me?

25:33.152 --> 25:34.719
Hey, you know what?

25:34.754 --> 25:36.154
Why don't you get washed up,
find your sister,

25:36.188 --> 25:38.290
all right,
before that chicken gets cold?

25:38.324 --> 25:41.092
Okay. Thanks for today,
Uncle Evan. You're the best.

25:41.127 --> 25:43.895
Aw.
So are you, buddy.

25:43.929 --> 25:45.730
You decked a guy?

25:45.765 --> 25:46.998
[ Laughs ]

25:47.033 --> 25:48.933
Got to teach that kid
about guys keeping secrets.

25:48.968 --> 25:50.802
That's not funny.
Evan, what happened?

25:50.836 --> 25:53.171
It was no big deal. Just a little
scuffle with some jerk.

25:53.205 --> 25:55.140
Okay, so wait a minute -- a guy
just came up out of the blue

25:55.174 --> 25:56.608
and decided that he wanted
to fight you?

25:56.642 --> 25:59.177
All right, it was...
an ex-boyfriend of Selena's.

25:59.211 --> 26:01.179
Seriously?
Did I not tell you?

26:01.213 --> 26:02.847
Don't worry.
I took care of it.

26:02.882 --> 26:04.182
Look, Evan,
you're a great guy,

26:04.216 --> 26:05.884
but you don't always
have to be the hero.

26:05.918 --> 26:08.386
I don't think
I always have to be the hero.

26:08.421 --> 26:11.323
And even if I was,
would that be such a bad thing?

26:11.357 --> 26:13.391
When it's for a lost cause,
it is.

26:13.426 --> 26:15.327
Well, you should know.
You've been doing it for years.

26:15.361 --> 26:17.395
Yep. Look what happened
to me.

26:19.565 --> 26:21.766
You know, I don't think
I'm hungry anymore.

26:21.801 --> 26:23.234
I'll see you later.

26:31.677 --> 26:34.312
Look, I'm telling you,
the financials don't add up.

26:34.347 --> 26:35.847
Or somebody at the bank
has got it wrong.

26:35.881 --> 26:37.782
No, you're the one
that has it wrong.

26:37.817 --> 26:39.184
Our savings is disappearing
faster than it's coming in.

26:39.218 --> 26:40.985
Now, will you sit down
and look at this, please?

26:41.020 --> 26:42.253
Stop putting this thing
in my face!

26:42.288 --> 26:44.923
Whoa.
Dude, take it easy.

26:44.957 --> 26:46.157
Hey,
you stay out of this.

26:46.192 --> 26:47.592
I don't even know
what's going on.

26:47.626 --> 26:49.794
I'm just saying
I think you should calm down.

26:49.829 --> 26:52.797
What is it with you, anyway --
always trying to be a hero?

26:52.832 --> 26:55.900
Nobody's trying
to be a hero here.

26:55.935 --> 26:57.902
Look, this is my family,
my life.

26:57.937 --> 26:59.371
I don't need you
coming up here,

26:59.405 --> 27:01.005
sticking your nose
in my business.

27:01.040 --> 27:03.975
You know what? I'm just gonna go
watch the game someplace else.

27:04.009 --> 27:05.577
Riley, you okay?
Yeah, she's good!

27:05.611 --> 27:07.846
Calm down!
Don't tell me to calm down!

27:07.880 --> 27:08.446
Evan!

27:12.885 --> 27:14.219
Why you always
looking after him?

27:14.253 --> 27:15.854
I just wanted to make sure
he was okay.

27:15.888 --> 27:16.888
Are you okay?

27:16.922 --> 27:17.956
Yeah.

27:17.990 --> 27:19.257
I'm fine.

27:35.300 --> 27:37.401
You know, I used to think
you were smart.

27:37.436 --> 27:39.170
I used to think a lot
about you.

27:39.204 --> 27:40.971
Now I just don't know you
anymore.

27:41.006 --> 27:42.807
Is there a question
hiding in there?

27:42.841 --> 27:44.408
What do you want
with Evan?

27:44.443 --> 27:46.277
Why is that
a concern of yours?

27:46.311 --> 27:47.645
Look,
if this is about Evan,

27:47.679 --> 27:49.647
why don't we just
leave things to him, okay?

27:49.681 --> 27:52.283
I think he's perfectly capable
of making his own choices.

27:52.317 --> 27:53.617
Got him fighting
your battles for you.

27:53.652 --> 27:55.152
Oh, yeah? How's that?

27:55.187 --> 27:56.320
He ran into one of
your old friends yesterday,

27:56.354 --> 27:57.521
and it got physical.

27:57.556 --> 27:59.523
Oh, yeah?

27:59.558 --> 28:01.258
That's kinda sweet.

28:01.293 --> 28:03.561
Glad to see you're concerned.
He's fine, by the way.

28:03.595 --> 28:05.229
You know, Riley,

28:05.263 --> 28:07.364
you may have some of the others
fooled around here.

28:07.399 --> 28:09.266
You may even have
some of them thinking

28:09.301 --> 28:11.802
that there's this big life
after leaving this place.

28:11.837 --> 28:14.238
There's a very big life
after leaving this place.

28:14.272 --> 28:16.140
You think this is
what I want to do?

28:16.174 --> 28:17.708
No, this is just
what I have to do.

28:17.742 --> 28:19.844
And right there is the
difference between you and me.

28:19.878 --> 28:22.379
You see, I know that there's
something better out there,

28:22.414 --> 28:24.882
and I know that I deserve it,
and I'm gonna go and get it.

28:24.916 --> 28:26.817
You -- you think
this is all you're worth.

28:26.852 --> 28:29.386
You know,
like you said,

28:29.421 --> 28:31.255
Evan is capable
of making his own decisions,

28:31.289 --> 28:32.990
even though he's had
a very long history

28:33.024 --> 28:34.992
of making the wrong ones
when it comes to women.

28:37.362 --> 28:39.296
You know,
that's all well and good,

28:39.331 --> 28:41.131
but you even
said it yourself --

28:41.166 --> 28:44.101
you don't know me anymore,
okay?

28:44.135 --> 28:47.004
You have no idea
what I'm capable of.

28:56.448 --> 28:58.482
[ Sighs ]
Is it time to go home yet?

28:58.517 --> 29:00.217
Even if it was
time to go home,

29:00.252 --> 29:02.286
it still wouldn't be
time to go home.

29:02.320 --> 29:04.221
It's ladies' night out,
remember?

29:04.256 --> 29:06.390
Oh,
I completely forgot.

29:06.424 --> 29:07.558
Sit down over there.

29:07.592 --> 29:09.527
[ Sighs ]
Okay, but I'm warning you,

29:09.561 --> 29:11.495
I may not be able
to get back up.

29:11.530 --> 29:12.997
What's making you
so tired?

29:13.031 --> 29:14.331
Worry.

29:14.366 --> 29:15.332
About what?

29:15.367 --> 29:16.800
Well, most recently,

29:16.835 --> 29:19.703
I told my mama that I would
help her buy her salon.

29:19.738 --> 29:21.305
Oh, that's so nice!

29:21.339 --> 29:23.407
It's just,
she's short on the financing,

29:23.441 --> 29:25.709
and so I told her
that I would be her partner

29:25.744 --> 29:28.746
and, you know, help her out
with the balance of the loan.

29:28.780 --> 29:30.648
So what's the problem?

29:30.682 --> 29:33.484
The bank wants to get
all up in my finances.

29:33.518 --> 29:34.818
Ohhhh.

29:34.853 --> 29:36.687
Yeah, I just don't want
to take the risk

29:36.721 --> 29:38.822
on getting myself
or this place in trouble.

29:38.857 --> 29:40.224
But what do I do
about my mama?

29:40.258 --> 29:43.327
I mean, owning the salon --
it's her dream.

29:43.361 --> 29:45.162
Hmm.

29:45.196 --> 29:46.964
Why don't you
just come out with us,

29:46.998 --> 29:48.566
at least
for a little while?

29:48.600 --> 29:50.701
You know, it might help you
sort things out.

29:50.735 --> 29:52.236
Where are you going?

29:52.270 --> 29:55.673
Saddle Ranch.
They put in a mechanical bull.

29:55.707 --> 29:57.441
Are you riding?

29:57.475 --> 29:59.777
[ Chuckling ] I never had
the courage to ride a real bull.

29:59.811 --> 30:01.712
I sure as hell ain't riding
no mechanical bull.

30:01.746 --> 30:03.480
[ Both laugh ]

30:03.515 --> 30:06.250
But we can have fun, you know,
watching everybody else.

30:07.786 --> 30:09.486
Oh, my gosh.

30:09.521 --> 30:10.487
That's it.

30:10.522 --> 30:11.455
Count me in.

30:14.793 --> 30:16.460
[ Rock music plays ]

30:16.494 --> 30:18.729
Whoo! Whoo!

30:18.763 --> 30:20.598
[ Screams ]

30:20.632 --> 30:22.666
[ Laughs ]

30:22.701 --> 30:24.268
Okay, ladies,

30:24.302 --> 30:26.437
let's show these boys
how drinking is done.

30:26.471 --> 30:27.404
[ Laughs ]

30:27.439 --> 30:28.405
Wait. Whiskey?

30:28.440 --> 30:29.506
I asked for a spritzer.

30:29.541 --> 30:30.507
Where's the ice?

30:30.542 --> 30:31.775
Neat or nothing!

30:31.810 --> 30:33.711
To the hottest women here!

30:33.745 --> 30:35.879
[ Glasses clink ]

30:35.914 --> 30:37.881
Be right back, y'all.

30:39.818 --> 30:41.485
Hey.
We got your message.

30:41.519 --> 30:42.786
What's going on?

30:42.821 --> 30:44.254
I thought maybe
we could see your form.

30:44.289 --> 30:45.789
You've already seen
his form.

30:47.492 --> 30:50.561
If you'll excuse me,
I'm gonna go take a little ride.

30:50.595 --> 30:51.662
Go on.

30:51.696 --> 30:53.664
[ Chuckles ]

30:53.698 --> 30:56.066
I just thought this might be
something Derek would like.

30:56.101 --> 30:58.636
Are you kidding?
It's his life.

30:58.670 --> 31:01.338
Good. That's the reason
I wanted to talk.

31:01.373 --> 31:02.840
Look, straight out --

31:02.874 --> 31:05.709
last time he was in the spa,
we didn't finish.

31:05.744 --> 31:08.946
Didn't mean anything.
He missed you.

31:08.980 --> 31:12.082
I miss him, too.

31:12.117 --> 31:14.118
Can't believe
I bought a vibrator.

31:15.220 --> 31:16.787
I haven't even
taken it out of the box.

31:16.821 --> 31:19.690
My husband --

31:19.724 --> 31:22.693
ex-husband...

31:22.727 --> 31:23.927
missing husband...?

31:23.962 --> 31:25.729
I don't even know
what he is.

31:25.764 --> 31:27.865
Um, anyway,
he was a big deal at U.T.

31:27.899 --> 31:29.433
Football was his life,

31:29.467 --> 31:31.435
and when he started
getting noticed from the pros,

31:31.469 --> 31:33.937
well, you would have thought
he just died and gone to heaven.

31:33.972 --> 31:37.541
Anyway, then Kyle got injured,
and that was that.

31:37.575 --> 31:40.778
His spirit broke the day
that he crushed his knee,

31:40.812 --> 31:42.880
and he was never
the same.

31:42.914 --> 31:45.549
He lost himself,
and I lost the man that I loved.

31:45.583 --> 31:47.818
Hmm.

31:47.852 --> 31:49.553
Men are complicated.

31:49.587 --> 31:51.121
Get more so every day.

31:52.857 --> 31:54.958
[ Crowd cheering ]

31:54.993 --> 31:56.560
[ Laughs ]

31:56.594 --> 31:58.128
Go on.

31:59.631 --> 32:00.731
Thank you.

32:02.567 --> 32:03.901
Jolene:
It's about time.

32:03.935 --> 32:05.636
Where you been?

32:05.670 --> 32:06.904
I'm sorry, but this hair
doesn't straighten itself.

32:06.938 --> 32:08.305
What is with the hat?

32:08.339 --> 32:09.573
Someone just
plopped it on head

32:09.607 --> 32:10.674
on the way back
from the ladies' room.

32:10.709 --> 32:12.009
You like it?

32:12.043 --> 32:13.644
That reminds me --
I got to pee.

32:13.678 --> 32:14.712
And no.

32:14.746 --> 32:16.413
So, are we
your final destination

32:16.448 --> 32:19.149
or just a pit stop
on your way to something better?

32:19.184 --> 32:20.884
Come on -- you know
there's always someplace better

32:20.919 --> 32:22.186
down the road for me.

32:22.220 --> 32:24.488
I'm gonna get
another drink, y'all.

32:26.424 --> 32:29.860
Okay, y'all, I think
I am gonna go home early,

32:29.894 --> 32:31.595
let the babysitter go.

32:31.629 --> 32:33.697
How would you like tomorrow off,
take care of your kids,

32:33.732 --> 32:35.666
take care of your mama,
take care of yourself?

32:35.700 --> 32:37.401
Uh,
I would say yes.

32:37.435 --> 32:38.836
Too bad
you can't afford it, huh?

32:38.870 --> 32:40.637
She can
if it's my treat.

32:40.672 --> 32:41.772
Really?

32:42.640 --> 32:44.374
Thank you, Georgia.

32:44.409 --> 32:45.375
Good night, you two.

32:45.410 --> 32:46.643
Night.
Bye.

32:48.747 --> 32:50.714
Hey. I was afraid
you'd left.

32:50.749 --> 32:53.484
Um... I wanted
to give this to you.

32:53.518 --> 32:54.551
Oh, thank you.

32:54.586 --> 32:56.720
Open it
when you get home.

32:56.755 --> 32:59.423
Thank you for
sticking your neck out for us --

32:59.457 --> 33:03.093
you know, for calling
me and Derek on our bullshit.

33:03.128 --> 33:05.162
Hey, I was there
with my husband once.

33:05.196 --> 33:07.397
Manipulation --
it's a powerful thing.

33:07.432 --> 33:08.766
[ Laughs ]

33:08.800 --> 33:09.767
Good night.
Good night.

33:12.003 --> 33:14.538
[ Crowd cheering ]

33:25.483 --> 33:27.351
[ Knock on door ]

33:31.422 --> 33:32.623
Since when do you knock?

33:32.657 --> 33:34.825
Trying to be respectful.

33:34.859 --> 33:36.693
Well, come on in.

33:38.963 --> 33:40.898
So, I was driving by,
and...

33:40.932 --> 33:42.466
I realized
we never did get a chance

33:42.500 --> 33:45.903
to talk about Travis
and...Winkie.

33:45.937 --> 33:47.504
Twinkle.
Whatever.

33:47.539 --> 33:48.939
You might want
to get that right

33:48.973 --> 33:50.741
if you're gonna keep
working for the Berkhalters.

33:50.775 --> 33:52.776
Good point.

33:52.811 --> 33:55.979
Well, turns out
it was nothing more than...

33:56.014 --> 33:58.916
a silly game they were
playing -- totally innocent.

33:58.950 --> 34:00.651
Yeah,
that's what I figured.

34:00.685 --> 34:02.653
That's what
my gut was telling me.

34:02.687 --> 34:04.154
Well, you've always had
a good gut.

34:04.189 --> 34:06.390
Well, thanks for talking to him,
nonetheless.

34:07.592 --> 34:09.592
Anytime.

34:09.627 --> 34:10.893
He's a good boy.

34:10.929 --> 34:12.663
Yeah.

34:12.697 --> 34:13.964
He is.

34:13.998 --> 34:15.666
I am gonna be late.

34:15.699 --> 34:18.202
Got so much free time,
I can't keep track of it.

34:20.505 --> 34:22.005
Bye, now.

34:45.719 --> 34:47.420
Is that whisker burn?

34:47.455 --> 34:49.255
But Duke has
a baby-smooth face.

34:49.290 --> 34:51.157
Aren't you always
telling us that?

34:51.192 --> 34:54.127
S-so, where'd you get
the whisker burn?

34:56.163 --> 34:58.364
Jolene, leave it alone!

34:58.399 --> 35:01.234
Oh,
you're seeing someone.

35:01.268 --> 35:03.203
He's the one
who sent you the flowers.

35:03.237 --> 35:05.171
He's the reason
you can't bring them home.

35:05.206 --> 35:06.706
What is your problem?

35:06.740 --> 35:09.375
Yes, I'm seeing another man,
but Duke doesn't care!

35:09.410 --> 35:12.745
It's an open relationship!
Or have you forgotten that?

35:12.780 --> 35:15.849
Georgia: How's everything
going in here? All right?

35:15.883 --> 35:18.852
You know, I can hear you
all the way down in reception.

35:18.886 --> 35:19.986
Sorry.
It's my fault.

35:20.020 --> 35:21.788
I don't care
whose fault it is.

35:21.822 --> 35:23.323
I'm just trying to figure out
what's going on with you two.

35:26.927 --> 35:27.861
I'm waiting.

35:27.895 --> 35:29.095
Are you serious?

35:29.130 --> 35:30.763
Well, if you're gonna
act like children,

35:30.798 --> 35:32.532
I intend to treat you
like children.

35:33.801 --> 35:36.769
I was nosing around
in Dee Ann's personal life.

35:36.804 --> 35:37.871
Is that it?

35:37.905 --> 35:40.707
Georgia,
really, it's fine.

35:42.176 --> 35:43.710
I wasn't being judgmental.

35:43.744 --> 35:47.046
I just...thought
that maybe I could help.

35:47.081 --> 35:48.148
Really.

35:49.917 --> 35:52.285
I know I come off as the
moral police. I don't mean to.

35:52.319 --> 35:53.987
I just...

35:54.021 --> 35:56.256
feel so different
from everyone else here.

35:56.290 --> 35:58.191
And I know
that doesn't even matter.

35:58.225 --> 36:01.394
What matters is that you know
that I care.

36:01.428 --> 36:02.295
And I do.

36:02.329 --> 36:04.164
Thank you.

36:04.198 --> 36:05.899
You're welcome.

36:05.933 --> 36:08.168
Just keep
your voices down.

36:10.371 --> 36:11.704
Like a morgue around here.

36:11.739 --> 36:13.806
How about
we listen to some music?

36:13.841 --> 36:15.041
Keep it low.

36:15.075 --> 36:16.910
Never mind.

36:16.944 --> 36:19.045
[ Sighs ]

36:20.047 --> 36:21.114
What?

36:25.019 --> 36:26.619
Well, how come
no one's saying anything?

36:30.057 --> 36:33.359
Oh. Riley told you about me
seeing her brother-in-law, huh?

36:34.495 --> 36:36.629
I know
she's not happy about this,

36:36.664 --> 36:39.432
but at this point,
I don't give a damn, okay?

36:39.466 --> 36:42.202
It started off
as something different,

36:42.236 --> 36:44.304
but...I don't know.

36:44.338 --> 36:48.608
I think I -- I think
I kinda like this guy.

36:52.213 --> 36:54.047
Oh, whatever!

37:01.255 --> 37:04.224
Look, this guy I'm seeing,
it's -- it's nothing.

37:04.258 --> 37:06.292
I-it's just fun.

37:06.327 --> 37:07.827
Just fun.

37:07.861 --> 37:09.796
Dee Ann, are you sure
this is a good idea?

37:11.565 --> 37:14.234
No. Probably not.

37:14.268 --> 37:15.602
I don't know.

37:15.636 --> 37:17.870
He's just --
he's so different from Duke.

37:17.905 --> 37:21.140
What if
it turns serious?

37:21.175 --> 37:23.009
It won't.

37:26.280 --> 37:27.847
What if it does?

37:29.617 --> 37:31.951
[ Voice breaking ]
I don't know.

37:44.498 --> 37:46.616
Riley, I hope that
you've managed to get

37:46.641 --> 37:47.967
Travis under control.

37:47.968 --> 37:50.603
I wouldn't like hearing
he's harassing other children.

37:50.638 --> 37:52.605
Travis doesn't need
to get under control.

37:52.640 --> 37:54.507
Neither does Twinkle.
You do.

37:54.541 --> 37:56.109
Excuse me?

37:56.143 --> 37:58.044
Oh, yeah, I heard
that you got all hysterical

37:58.078 --> 38:00.613
and made a mountain
out of a molehill again.

38:00.648 --> 38:02.148
I doubt that.

38:02.182 --> 38:03.383
Look, you can believe
whatever you want,

38:03.417 --> 38:05.184
but our kids
are perfectly normal,

38:05.219 --> 38:07.253
and nothing was going on
between them.

38:07.288 --> 38:08.554
You know what?

38:08.589 --> 38:10.456
I have a surprise
for you.

38:16.530 --> 38:18.231
It's a vibrator.

38:18.265 --> 38:19.866
Loosen up, Taylor.

38:23.537 --> 38:25.104
Riley,
before you go out there,

38:25.139 --> 38:27.573
your mama got some bad news
from the bank today.

38:27.608 --> 38:30.443
Even with the money
you wanted to give her,

38:30.477 --> 38:32.345
she won't be able
to outbid the Berkhalters.

38:32.379 --> 38:33.846
[ Sighing ] Oh, boy.

38:33.881 --> 38:35.515
Okay.
Let's go cheer her up.

38:35.549 --> 38:36.582
Okay.

38:38.152 --> 38:40.186
Hey, mama.

38:40.220 --> 38:42.555
Lacey just told me.
I'm so sorry.

38:42.589 --> 38:43.656
Hey,
there's my partner.

38:43.691 --> 38:44.624
But you're not getting
the loan.

38:44.658 --> 38:46.225
You're still my partner.

38:46.260 --> 38:48.127
Yes, mama, I am.

38:48.162 --> 38:49.429
Sit down, Lacey.

38:51.565 --> 38:52.999
Oh, this could be
so much fun.

38:53.033 --> 38:55.501
I'm thinking about ways
to spruce up the place --

38:55.536 --> 38:56.869
maybe even add
a new coat of paint.

38:56.904 --> 38:58.338
What do you think
of seafoam?

38:58.372 --> 39:01.207
Studies say that green has
a calming influence.

39:01.241 --> 39:02.842
I thought that was blue.

39:02.876 --> 39:04.944
Well, anyway,
just for one day, y'all,

39:04.978 --> 39:07.146
let's pretend
the salon is mine, okay?

39:07.181 --> 39:08.181
What will we do?

39:13.554 --> 39:17.223
♪ Hold on to hope, love

39:17.257 --> 39:24.197
♪ I searched high and low
for you ♪

39:24.231 --> 39:25.064
♪ for you

39:27.701 --> 39:31.904
